def: A earthworm of the genus Lumbricus, frequently used by anglersfor bait. See Earthworm.
A stroller; a loiterer; esp., an idle, untidy woman; aslattern; a slut; a whore.
Suitable for exportation; as, exportable products.

That which rectifies or refines; esp., a part of a distillingapparatus in which the more volatile portions are separated from theless volatile by the process of evaporation and condensation; arectifier.
Defensive armor for the thighs. [ Written also cuisse, andquish.]
An ancient instrument resembling the harp.
Destitute of a home.-- Home"less*ness, n.
To reprimand; to sneap. [Obs.] "Scold and sneb the good oak."Spenser.
One who, or that which, pacifies; a peacemaker.  Bacon.

A love-singer; specifically, one of a class of German poets andmusicians who flourished from about the middle of the twelfth to themiddle of the fourteenth century. They were chiefly of noble birth,and made love and beauty the subjects of their verses.
Pertaining to, or secreting, cerumen; as, the ceruminousglands.
